1
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:28,733
(Usagi)
Isn't it beautiful?

2
00:00:28,766 --> 00:00:33,100
I can't wait to wear a dress
like that when Mamo and I
finally get married.

3
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:34,333
Yeah, me too!

4
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:37,100
Hey! Mamo's all mine.
Remember that.

5
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:38,500
[nervous laugh]

6
00:00:38,566 --> 00:00:42,166
But still, wearing a gorgeous
wedding dress is every girl's
dream!

7
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:44,266
Does that mean becoming
a bride is your dream?

8
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:46,466
M‐hmm! Don't you
want to get married?

9
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:48,500
Oh yeah, definitely!

10
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,733
But... I have
other dreams too.

11
00:00:50,766 --> 00:00:54,600
I want to be a flight attendant,
kindergarten teacher, actress,
and a fashion model.

12
00:00:54,633 --> 00:00:56,600
Uh‐huh...

13
00:00:56,633 --> 00:00:58,333
[scream]
What is it?

14
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:01,073
I totally forgot! "RanRan"
goes on sale today!

15
00:01:01,106 --> 00:01:02,606
Is it that big a deal?

16
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:04,306
So cute!

17
00:01:04,340 --> 00:01:09,739
I bet it's awesome being on the
cover of a magazine. That would
be a great dream too!

18
00:01:09,773 --> 00:01:11,673
Usagi... Hey, Usagi!

19
00:01:11,740 --> 00:01:13,773
Not now. I'm
busy daydreaming.

20
00:01:13,806 --> 00:01:14,673
Look!

21
00:01:14,740 --> 00:01:16,340
Hm?

22
00:01:16,406 --> 00:01:18,273
Whaaaat!?

23
00:01:18,306 --> 00:01:20,840
<i>...No way!</i>

24
00:01:24,673 --> 00:01:34,940
♪

25
00:01:34,940 --> 00:01:54,940
♪

26
00:01:54,940 --> 00:02:14,946
♪

27
00:02:14,946 --> 00:02:34,846
♪

28
00:02:34,846 --> 00:02:53,513
♪

29
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:04,853
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>Flames of Passion: Mars's</i>
<i>Raging Super Attack</i>

30
00:03:08,253 --> 00:03:09,953
(Rei)
Here you go...!
(Man)
Thank you!

31
00:03:09,953 --> 00:03:10,953
(Rei)
And here's yours!

32
00:03:10,986 --> 00:03:13,086
I hope you fall in love
with someone very special.

33
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:13,786
Thanks!

34
00:03:13,853 --> 00:03:15,520
Hiya, Rei. Can I
get one, please?

35
00:03:15,586 --> 00:03:16,786
Me too!

36
00:03:16,820 --> 00:03:17,953
I was here first!

37
00:03:17,953 --> 00:03:19,586
No you weren't!

38
00:03:19,620 --> 00:03:22,986
Please, boys. There's no need to
fight! You're putting me in a
tough spot here.

39
00:03:23,020 --> 00:03:25,986
"You're putting me in a
tough spot." What an act.

40
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:27,520
...Yeah...

41
00:03:27,586 --> 00:03:29,753
All this from
one magazine?

42
00:03:29,786 --> 00:03:31,953
That's the power
of the press.

43
00:03:31,953 --> 00:03:33,920
Rei sure is popular.

44
00:03:34,586 --> 00:03:36,620
Thank you everyone!
Have a nice day!

45
00:03:36,620 --> 00:03:38,020
I'll come back
again tomorrow!

46
00:03:38,086 --> 00:03:41,520
I'll be waiting for you!

47
00:03:41,586 --> 00:03:42,853
"I'll be waiting for you!"

48
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,586
Why, hello there!

49
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:45,686
Drop the act.

50
00:03:45,753 --> 00:03:47,486
We saw the
magazine article!

51
00:03:47,553 --> 00:03:52,753
"The most popular item sold at
Hikawa Shrine is the amulet that
promises love and romance."

52
00:03:52,786 --> 00:03:57,653
"These amulets, when offered by
a beautiful shrine maiden, give
their owner mystical power."

53
00:03:57,686 --> 00:04:00,753
Is this "beautiful" shrine
maiden supposed to be you?

54
00:04:00,786 --> 00:04:04,626
Someone from the magazine
visited us the other day and
insisted on an interview.

55
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:08,126
What can I say? He knows a
great story when he sees one.

56
00:04:08,126 --> 00:04:11,826
I don't remember Hikawa
Shrine amulets being so popular.
|

57
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:13,460
It's all a scam.

58
00:04:13,493 --> 00:04:14,793
Hold on, I'm confused.

59
00:04:14,826 --> 00:04:18,426
Yeah, you don't sell the
amulets. That's Yuichiro's job.

60
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:21,993
You're right. All I said was
our best‐seller at the shrine
is our love amulet.

61
00:04:22,026 --> 00:04:25,460
But they assumed that meant I
sold them. You can't blame me
for that.

62
00:04:25,493 --> 00:04:28,593
Besides, what's the harm in
playing the role of "beautiful
shrine maiden?"

63
00:04:28,626 --> 00:04:30,593
Who knows? Maybe I can
keep this trend going!

64
00:04:30,626 --> 00:04:35,426
Then we'd become super popular
and famous. We'd be known as
"Hikawa Shrine, the shrine of
love,"

65
00:04:35,459 --> 00:04:36,859
and we'd get a ton
more visitors.

66
00:04:36,926 --> 00:04:39,093
Then I could record and
release my own pop album!

67
00:04:39,126 --> 00:04:40,626
(All)
Get real!

68
00:04:40,626 --> 00:04:43,526
I don't know what I'll
do with all this fame.

69
00:04:43,593 --> 00:04:45,126
She's lost her mind.

70
00:04:45,193 --> 00:04:49,093
I have a vision for my life, a
dream of taking my personal
brand worldwide.

71
00:04:49,126 --> 00:04:54,960
<i>(Usagi)</i>
<i>I'll travel the globe... as</i>
<i>an icon of success!</i>

72
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:56,460
[cheering]

73
00:04:56,493 --> 00:04:58,426
Well? What happened
to that dream?

74
00:04:58,460 --> 00:05:00,026
I've got it all figured out.

75
00:05:00,093 --> 00:05:02,433
I don't think you are
being very realistic.

76
00:05:02,466 --> 00:05:05,633
Well, that's 'cause ordinary
girls like you can't dream big!

77
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:07,300
Yeah!? And what's
so special about you?

78
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:12,433
Oh, my dear, isn't it obvious?
I have something that you lack:
irresistible beauty.

79
00:05:12,466 --> 00:05:14,633
If you mean "beauty
sleep" then, okay.

80
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:17,433
I'm not the one who sleeps
through her alarm every day!

81
00:05:17,466 --> 00:05:19,666
Not every day!
Only three days
a week max!

82
00:05:19,700 --> 00:05:20,833
They're at it again...

83
00:05:20,866 --> 00:05:22,533
Let's hide at a safe distance
and wait 'til they're done.

84
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:27,033
Excuse me. Do any of you happen
to know where I can I find the
mystical shrine maiden?

85
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:29,866
Uh, hello...?

86
00:05:29,933 --> 00:05:31,966
And you are...?

87
00:05:31,966 --> 00:05:37,633
My name's Nanako. I was inspired
by the magazine article so I
came here to meet the famous
shrine maiden.

88
00:05:37,633 --> 00:05:41,666
Miss Rei is my new role model,
I want to be just like her!

89
00:05:41,700 --> 00:05:44,766
[fighting grunts]

90
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,966
I'm your role model?
Oh my goodness.

91
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,366
[giggle]

92
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:53,466
It's you! I wanna be a
shrine maiden just like you!

93
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,633
Can I work here? Please,
please, can I?

94
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:57,500
Good publicity works wonders.

95
00:05:57,533 --> 00:05:59,800
Now "shrine maiden"
is a career goal.

96
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:02,640
You mean it?! Wow,
this is great!

97
00:06:02,673 --> 00:06:04,973
Thank you! Thank
you so much!

98
00:06:06,540 --> 00:06:11,873
Yes, your Loveliness... I need
just a little more time. That is
all.

99
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:16,873
Then we will be able to welcome
you into this unworthy world,
in all your glory!

100
00:06:16,940 --> 00:06:22,373
Yes, yes I promise! Very soon!

101
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:26,606
Ah, you've returned.

102
00:06:26,640 --> 00:06:28,273
How did it go?

103
00:06:28,306 --> 00:06:32,606
Oh, excellent. This girl?

104
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:35,606
I don't sense a dream in
her, she looks empty.

105
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:39,340
Are you positive this
human is the one we want?

106
00:06:41,606 --> 00:06:44,673
Girls! Where are you?

107
00:06:44,706 --> 00:06:46,473
[gasp]

108
00:06:46,473 --> 00:06:47,973
What's up, Granny?

109
00:06:48,006 --> 00:06:51,940
[giggling]

110
00:06:51,973 --> 00:06:54,306
Enough! Stop playing around!

111
00:06:54,306 --> 00:06:56,140
But we weren't playing.

112
00:06:56,140 --> 00:07:00,540
Isn't it obvious? We're testing
out new tricks to impress the
crowds when we enter the ring.

113
00:07:00,606 --> 00:07:04,646
We need to improve our circus
act if we want our audience to
come back for more.

114
00:07:04,646 --> 00:07:07,680
We're hard workers. Not
lazy like you, Granny.

115
00:07:07,713 --> 00:07:09,646
Appearing out of
smoke is so over!

116
00:07:09,646 --> 00:07:16,680
Impudence! You will learn to
respect me and follow my orders.
That's what you girls need to
do!

117
00:07:16,713 --> 00:07:19,813
<i>This is your next target... now</i>
<i>listen carefully to me...</i>

118
00:07:19,813 --> 00:07:21,813
‐Lemme see...
‐She's still a kid!

119
00:07:21,846 --> 00:07:23,813
Would a girl like this
have the Golden Mirror?

120
00:07:23,846 --> 00:07:25,880
I dunno, this
seems real dumb.

121
00:07:25,946 --> 00:07:28,880
Silence! Enough with your
tiresome prattle.

122
00:07:28,946 --> 00:07:31,446
It's time for you
to do your job!

123
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:35,280
Find the person with the Golden
Mirror. Find where Pegasus is
hiding!

124
00:07:36,446 --> 00:07:37,780
(Rei)
Here! Enjoy your
love amulet.

125
00:07:37,813 --> 00:07:40,646
<i>(Nanako)</i>
<i>I hope you fall in love with</i>
<i>someone very special.</i>

126
00:07:40,646 --> 00:07:44,480
Me too! You have such a cute
little sister, Rei. She's
adorable!

127
00:07:44,513 --> 00:07:49,213
Yeah, just looking at you two
gives me hope that my luck'll
change and I'll find true love.

128
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:52,680
With that kind of positive
spirit, I'm sure you will,
very soon!

129
00:07:52,713 --> 00:07:55,646
Really? Then I'll come for
inspiration every day.

130
00:07:55,646 --> 00:07:57,546
We'll be here waiting.

131
00:07:57,613 --> 00:07:58,813
Thank you.

132
00:08:04,186 --> 00:08:06,653
<i>(Nanako)</i>
<i>Thanks for visiting!</i>
<i>Come back soon!</i>

133
00:08:06,653 --> 00:08:08,653
(Boy)
I think I'm in love
with the shrine maiden!

134
00:08:08,653 --> 00:08:10,886
Yeah! Other girls
can't even compare.

135
00:08:10,953 --> 00:08:12,786
Did you hear that, girls?

136
00:08:12,820 --> 00:08:16,553
Hel‐lo? There are five
wonderful, pretty girls
right over here!

137
00:08:16,620 --> 00:08:21,220
So, uh, do you think the Hikawa
Shrine's amulets actually have
love powers?

138
00:08:21,286 --> 00:08:23,853
Come on, Ami!

139
00:08:23,886 --> 00:08:26,853
Just think, if they
did then Rei...

140
00:08:26,886 --> 00:08:30,153
...should've had a boyfriend
ages ago! [laughter]

141
00:08:30,186 --> 00:08:32,153
Looks like they're
working now.

142
00:08:35,486 --> 00:08:38,153
Maybe I'll go help her
out as a shrine maiden.

143
00:08:38,153 --> 00:08:40,286
Yeah, that's a great idea.

144
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:43,353
Rei said she could use all the
extra help she can get, right?

145
00:08:43,386 --> 00:08:47,486
Actually, she said Nanako's a
hard worker, so one helper is
all she needs.

146
00:08:47,486 --> 00:08:49,186
[groans]
Good point...

147
00:08:49,220 --> 00:08:52,153
<i>Nanako's totally</i>
<i>into it‐‐wig and all.</i>

148
00:08:52,186 --> 00:08:53,453
[sad sighs]

149
00:08:53,486 --> 00:08:56,453
Excuse me...

150
00:08:56,486 --> 00:08:57,820
Yes...?

151
00:08:57,853 --> 00:08:58,686
Can we...

152
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:00,493
...help you with something?

153
00:09:00,526 --> 00:09:01,560
We just scored!
Yeah!

154
00:09:01,626 --> 00:09:04,460
Oh my gosh he's so hot. I
can't believe our luck.

155
00:09:04,493 --> 00:09:07,326
Yeah! So, how do we do this? We
all want to date him, right?

156
00:09:07,326 --> 00:09:09,226
Maybe for starters
a group date, then!

157
00:09:09,293 --> 00:09:10,793
<i>(Handsome Man)</i>
<i>Thank you very much.</i>

158
00:09:10,826 --> 00:09:11,993
<i>(Ami)</i>
<i>My pleasure, see ya!</i>

159
00:09:12,060 --> 00:09:13,126
‐What just happened?
‐What just happened?
‐What just happened?

160
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:16,726
He wanted directions to the
Juban Hawaiian Center.

161
00:09:16,793 --> 00:09:18,226
‐Say what?
‐Say what?
‐Say what?

162
00:09:18,293 --> 00:09:19,560
There's a "Hawaiian Center"?

163
00:09:19,626 --> 00:09:20,493
Sure!

164
00:09:20,526 --> 00:09:21,660
[groans]

165
00:09:21,693 --> 00:09:25,460
I'm sorry I have to put you
on clean up duty with me.

166
00:09:25,493 --> 00:09:29,493
You don't need to apologize.
I'm happy just being with you,
Miss Rei.

167
00:09:29,526 --> 00:09:30,726
[chuckle]

168
00:09:30,793 --> 00:09:34,026
This job's a chance for me to
learn from an inspiration.

169
00:09:34,060 --> 00:09:36,326
You're a woman who's
smart and beautiful!

170
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:38,626
Plus you've achieved your dream
of being a shrine maiden!

171
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:40,226
<i>Your future is set!</i>

172
00:09:40,293 --> 00:09:42,060
Nanako, I should tell you...

173
00:09:42,126 --> 00:09:44,326
I want to be a shrine maiden,
just like you!

174
00:09:44,326 --> 00:09:47,060
I wonder what it's like to
make a dream come true.

175
00:09:47,126 --> 00:09:51,393
It must feel great!
So I'm gonna help you and make
my dream the same as yours!

176
00:09:51,460 --> 00:09:54,160
Nanako, that's
very nice, but...

177
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:59,160
I'll work as hard as I can, I
promise, so I can be like you
someday.

178
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:01,100
Please let me stay here!

179
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:06,733
[sigh] When I'm with you,
I feel like life is easier.

180
00:10:06,766 --> 00:10:09,600
,,,like I'm with
a big sister.

181
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,566
[gasp]

182
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,933
Okay! Back to work!

183
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:18,500
[sigh]

184
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:23,266
Her "big sister"...

185
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:29,100
Nanako sure works hard...

186
00:10:29,133 --> 00:10:30,566
Yeah...

187
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:33,300
...but wanting to be a shrine
maiden just because she idolizes
Rei...?

188
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:34,966
...that's pretty unusual.

189
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:39,566
Especially when Rei hasn't
decided if she'll continue
working here at the shrine.

190
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,100
Lemme talk to Nanako.

191
00:10:41,133 --> 00:10:42,600
Wait!

192
00:10:42,633 --> 00:10:43,933
Good grief.

193
00:10:43,966 --> 00:10:47,300
There she goes again,
meddling in other people's
private business.

194
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:49,100
But being nosy looks fun!

195
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:51,100
‐Diana...
‐Diana...

196
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:52,333
Nanako...

197
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:53,100
Oh, Usagi!

198
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:54,333
So, how are
you liking it here?

199
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:57,600
Working with Rei is great! I
feel so lucky to be around her.

200
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:01,340
She's like a big sister and role
model rolled into one perfect
person!

201
00:11:01,406 --> 00:11:03,606
She's pure, honest,
And best of all...

202
00:11:03,606 --> 00:11:08,973
she's devoted the rest of her
life to staying here at the
shrine, and praying for other
people's happiness.

203
00:11:09,006 --> 00:11:14,006
That doesn't sound like the Rei
I know. Doesn't she usually put
her own happiness first?

204
00:11:14,073 --> 00:11:18,773
Yeah. Nanako, do you have any
dreams ‐ besides helping Rei
make her dream come true?

205
00:11:18,773 --> 00:11:22,340
Chibi‐Usa, you're still
too young to understand
this kind of thing.

206
00:11:22,406 --> 00:11:25,640
See, there are dreams that come
true, and dreams that never
will.

207
00:11:25,673 --> 00:11:29,106
It's sad, but my dreams are all
the kind that won't come true.

208
00:11:29,140 --> 00:11:32,473
I'm sure they can come true.
You just have to work hard to
achieve them.

209
00:11:32,506 --> 00:11:34,473
Yeah, that's right,
even Rei...

210
00:11:34,506 --> 00:11:36,906
Rei's one and only dream is to
be the maiden for this shrine.

211
00:11:36,940 --> 00:11:43,640
That's better than my own stupid
dreams. So I'm going to follow
in her footsteps. I'll remain
single forever, just like her!

212
00:11:43,673 --> 00:11:47,340
‐Wait a sec...
‐Single...?

213
00:11:47,406 --> 00:11:50,440
Does she mean not having a
boyfriend or a husband?

214
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,740
Mhm!

215
00:11:51,773 --> 00:11:53,973
That's right! I'm going
to remain dedicated to
this shrine ‐‐

216
00:11:54,006 --> 00:11:56,273
(Ves‐Ves)
Hang on... Is that
girl the target?

217
00:11:56,306 --> 00:11:59,673
She's wearing a wig, that's why
I had a hard time finding her!

218
00:11:59,740 --> 00:12:01,413
Got ya now! [giggle]

219
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:14,280
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

220
00:12:18,980 --> 00:12:27,480
<i>♪ Sailor Moon</i>

221
00:12:29,146 --> 00:12:30,913
<i>(Rei)</i>
<i>She thinks what!?</i>

222
00:12:30,946 --> 00:12:34,580
I said, Nanako thinks you're
going to stay single for the
rest of your life because you've

223
00:12:34,613 --> 00:12:37,313
achieved your 1 dream of
being a shrine maiden.

224
00:12:37,346 --> 00:12:39,513
That's totally ridiculous!
Where did she get that idea!?

225
00:12:39,580 --> 00:12:45,446
I don't know, but maybe it's
because shrine maidens have a
reputation for dedicating their
lives to the gods.

226
00:12:45,446 --> 00:12:46,946
She makes a good point.

227
00:12:46,946 --> 00:12:49,413
But that's not
Rei's dream, is it?

228
00:12:49,446 --> 00:12:53,413
Darn right! My potential's
unlimited and I plan to do
many things!

229
00:12:53,446 --> 00:12:58,846
I want to experience lots of
love, find a great man, become
happily married, and have a
successful career!

230
00:12:58,913 --> 00:13:04,086
I have a vision for my life, a
dream of taking my personal
brand worldwide.

231
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:07,086
I'll travel the globe...

232
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:10,120
as an icon of success!

233
00:13:10,153 --> 00:13:14,286
Yeah, maybe you say that. But
you seem happy with local fame.

234
00:13:14,286 --> 00:13:18,320
Well, of course! People from
across the country are coming
here just to see me.

235
00:13:18,353 --> 00:13:20,920
It's flattering and wonderful
and humbling too.

236
00:13:20,953 --> 00:13:24,453
But I won't be pigeon holed as a
small‐time shrine maiden my
whole life.

237
00:13:24,486 --> 00:13:25,520
[groans]

238
00:13:25,586 --> 00:13:27,286
There's the Rei
we know and love!

239
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:30,120
So you're just pretending to be
a shrine maiden role model.

240
00:13:30,153 --> 00:13:33,586
Even when she said, "You're like
a big sister to me!"

241
00:13:33,620 --> 00:13:37,120
For a moment, I thought you were
taking all of her puppy love
seriously.

242
00:13:37,153 --> 00:13:39,320
...Were you...

243
00:13:39,353 --> 00:13:42,453
Leave me alone! I was just
being nice ‐‐ trying to
support Nanako's dream!

244
00:13:42,453 --> 00:13:46,353
But it's not Nanako's dream,
she's following yours.

245
00:13:46,420 --> 00:13:47,820
Mhm.

246
00:13:47,853 --> 00:13:49,653
She doesn't have a dream?

247
00:13:49,686 --> 00:13:55,520
She said her dreams are too big
to come true. So she just wants
to be like you at the shrine.

248
00:13:55,586 --> 00:13:59,453
But this whole time I thought
her dream was to become a shrine
maiden. Was she lying to me?

249
00:13:59,453 --> 00:14:04,293
She said her dreams are stupid
and she wants to dedicate
herself to a quiet life.

250
00:14:04,293 --> 00:14:06,860
That's crazy. This changes
everything!

251
00:14:06,926 --> 00:14:09,526
Nanako told me she wanted to
become a shrine maiden.

252
00:14:09,593 --> 00:14:13,093
Rei...
<i>That's why I said she could help</i>
<i>me, even if she got off on the</i>
<i>wrong foot.</i>

253
00:14:13,126 --> 00:14:14,660
Off on the wrong foot?

254
00:14:14,726 --> 00:14:18,826
But I think she's got a much
bigger problem than idolizing
me. Much bigger!

255
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:22,260
She's using the shrine as way to
avoid following her own dreams.

256
00:14:22,293 --> 00:14:24,126
Master Ami!

257
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,626
<i>(Rei)</i>
<i>You can't be a shrine maiden</i>
<i>because you're scared of</i>
<i>living your own life!</i>

258
00:14:25,626 --> 00:14:29,126
Our job is to give people
dreams! To keep their hopes
alive!

259
00:14:29,126 --> 00:14:32,093
But without dreams of her own,
she's no shrine maiden.

260
00:14:32,126 --> 00:14:33,926
Rei, don't say it!

261
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,493
I don't want her around me!

262
00:14:35,526 --> 00:14:40,026
[gasps]

263
00:14:40,093 --> 00:14:44,126
I... I'm sorry. I didn't mean
to offend you...

264
00:14:44,126 --> 00:14:48,193
I was just trying to be like
you, Rei...

265
00:14:48,260 --> 00:14:51,460
Someone that's strong and
beautiful...

266
00:14:51,460 --> 00:14:53,326
I'm sorry!

267
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:54,793
Nanako!

268
00:14:54,793 --> 00:14:56,460
Rei, go talk to her!

269
00:14:56,460 --> 00:14:58,093
It won't change anything/

270
00:14:58,126 --> 00:14:59,466
Nanako!

271
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:00,833
Let's go!

272
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:09,366
[sob] I can't... There's no way
I'll chase my dreams!

273
00:15:09,433 --> 00:15:11,433
What!? Hold on...

274
00:15:11,466 --> 00:15:13,933
Are you telling me
you don't have a dream?

275
00:15:13,966 --> 00:15:15,466
No, I... It's none of your
business.

276
00:15:15,466 --> 00:15:19,033
Of course it is! You really
don't have any dreams?

277
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:22,133
Leave me alone. My dreams are
over and I'm all alone, with no
direction.

278
00:15:22,166 --> 00:15:23,933
I'm totally empty!

279
00:15:23,966 --> 00:15:26,200
What?! This is just awful!

280
00:15:26,266 --> 00:15:28,300
A girl with no dream
is a loser...!

281
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:32,100
Get it together! This is no time
for crying in a puddle of
self‐pity!

282
00:15:32,133 --> 00:15:34,133
You must have some
dream... now think!

283
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:36,666
I don't want to.
Please just go away.

284
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:39,766
Aw jeez, this is why I can't
rely on what Granny tells me.

285
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,133
Today is not my day.

286
00:15:41,166 --> 00:15:42,500
There is one thing...

287
00:15:42,533 --> 00:15:45,833
Let go. I don't have time for a
girl who doesn't have any
dreams.

288
00:15:45,866 --> 00:15:47,300
I do have a dream!

289
00:15:48,933 --> 00:15:50,433
Oh?

290
00:15:50,466 --> 00:15:55,000
But, my dream is way too big.
It's so big I know it'll never
come true!

291
00:15:55,033 --> 00:15:59,206
That's great! Then let's have
a look at your Dream Mirror!

292
00:16:01,806 --> 00:16:03,373
Orb Shot!

293
00:16:05,473 --> 00:16:06,940
[scream]

294
00:16:08,940 --> 00:16:10,640
Come on come on!

295
00:16:13,173 --> 00:16:16,806
A blank mirror? Damn
that flying eyeball!

296
00:16:16,840 --> 00:16:20,273
<i>(Sailor Moon)</i>
<i>Hold it right there!</i>

297
00:16:20,306 --> 00:16:23,340
How dare you bully a young
girl...

298
00:16:23,373 --> 00:16:25,373
who's struggling
with her dreams!

299
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:27,173
As long as there is evil
in this world...

300
00:16:27,206 --> 00:16:30,140
we, the Sailor Guardians...

301
00:16:30,173 --> 00:16:32,340
are here to beat
bad guys like you.

302
00:16:32,373 --> 00:16:35,340
In the name of the Moon...

303
00:16:35,373 --> 00:16:37,806
‐We'll punish you!
‐We'll punish you!

304
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:39,806
Some uninvited guests.

305
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:44,773
Come forth, my Lemures!
Mane‐Mane Girl, the
Dream‐Eating Monkey.

306
00:16:48,873 --> 00:16:50,973
Mane‐Mane Mane‐Mane Mane!

307
00:16:51,006 --> 00:16:53,640
Mane‐Mane Girl, go take care
of those brats. Now!

308
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:56,006
"Mane‐Mane Girl, go take care
of those brats. Now! "

309
00:16:56,040 --> 00:16:58,806
Hey! Stop imitating me,
and attack already!

310
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:01,346
Mane! Stop imitating me, and
attack already!

311
00:17:01,380 --> 00:17:02,646
[grunts]

312
00:17:02,646 --> 00:17:04,813
Mane‐Mane Mane‐Mane Mane!

313
00:17:04,846 --> 00:17:08,346
Try this on‐‐ Venus
Love Me Chain!

314
00:17:08,380 --> 00:17:10,980
[grunt]

315
00:17:11,146 --> 00:17:12,146
Mane!

316
00:17:12,180 --> 00:17:13,813
That's me!

317
00:17:13,846 --> 00:17:17,213
Mane‐Mane, Love Me Chain!

318
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:18,880
[screams]

319
00:17:18,946 --> 00:17:22,146
Sparkling Wide Pressure!

320
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:24,013
Mane‐Mane‐Mane!

321
00:17:24,046 --> 00:17:25,780
It's Jupiter!

322
00:17:25,813 --> 00:17:27,046
A spitting image!

323
00:17:27,113 --> 00:17:28,113
Uh‐huh!

324
00:17:28,346 --> 00:17:29,646
[groan]

325
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:32,146
Mane! Sparkling Wide Pressure!

326
00:17:32,180 --> 00:17:33,813
[screams]

327
00:17:33,813 --> 00:17:35,880
Mane‐Mane Mane‐Mane!

328
00:17:35,946 --> 00:17:36,813
Mercury...!

329
00:17:36,846 --> 00:17:38,346
(All)
No!!

330
00:17:38,380 --> 00:17:41,946
Just kidding! Looks like she can
mimic our attacks and use them
against us.

331
00:17:41,980 --> 00:17:43,980
We'll end up
destroying ourselves.

332
00:17:43,980 --> 00:17:45,646
So how do we defeat her?

333
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:48,046
Mane! So how do we defeat her?

334
00:17:48,113 --> 00:17:50,280
Master Rei. This way!

335
00:17:50,313 --> 00:17:53,880
Hey Mane‐Mane, time to
claim your reward.

336
00:17:53,946 --> 00:17:56,313
Now go eat that girl's
Dream mirror.

337
00:17:56,313 --> 00:17:58,980
[shouting]

338
00:17:59,013 --> 00:18:00,186
[gasps]

339
00:18:00,220 --> 00:18:02,153
[gasp]

340
00:18:02,186 --> 00:18:04,153
I have a dream, too y'know...

341
00:18:04,153 --> 00:18:06,286
It's Nanako!?

342
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:11,320
I want to find a wonderful
boyfriend! And I want to make a
career for myself by flying all
around the world!

343
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:14,653
My dream is to live a fabulous
life as an icon of success!

344
00:18:14,653 --> 00:18:15,720
Nanako!

345
00:18:15,786 --> 00:18:18,186
But I don't have the
courage to pursue my dreams.

346
00:18:18,220 --> 00:18:21,786
I'm scared of failure, and I
hate so many things about
myself.

347
00:18:21,820 --> 00:18:23,620
<i>I want to become someone else...</i>

348
00:18:23,786 --> 00:18:29,153
<i>I thought that if I could become</i>
<i>like my idol, Rei, all my fears</i>
<i>and worries would disappear.</i>

349
00:18:29,153 --> 00:18:33,553
<i>I could become a new me.</i>
<i>I really believed that.</i>

350
00:18:33,620 --> 00:18:35,220
Nanako...

351
00:18:35,286 --> 00:18:37,220
Please stop, I'm so ashamed.

352
00:18:37,286 --> 00:18:38,720
[grunt]

353
00:18:38,786 --> 00:18:44,653
Mars Crystal Power Make Up!

354
00:18:49,986 --> 00:18:59,126
♪

355
00:19:01,226 --> 00:19:04,126
<i>I'm a loser. My dream</i>
<i>will never come true!</i>

356
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:06,293
<i>Okay, we get it.</i>
<i>You're pathetic!</i>

357
00:19:06,326 --> 00:19:07,526
<i>(Mars)</i>
<i>That's enough!</i>

358
00:19:08,293 --> 00:19:12,026
You've gobbled up
this girl's dream.

359
00:19:12,060 --> 00:19:14,560
How dare you ape her when she's
down! In the name of Mars,
I'll chastise you!

360
00:19:14,626 --> 00:19:18,126
Nice try but we won't let you
steal the spotlight. Mane‐Mane!

361
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,560
I'll chastise you!

362
00:19:19,626 --> 00:19:20,893
Stop imitating me!

363
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:21,493
Sailor Mars!

364
00:19:21,526 --> 00:19:22,160
Wait, don't!

365
00:19:22,193 --> 00:19:23,726
She'll mimic your powers!

366
00:19:23,793 --> 00:19:25,026
Mane‐Mane Mane‐Mane!

367
00:19:25,060 --> 00:19:27,993
Burning Mandala!

368
00:19:29,060 --> 00:19:30,793
Mane‐Mane Mandala!

369
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:32,126
[gasps]

370
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:35,026
Mimicking someone else's
moves to win is cheating!

371
00:19:35,060 --> 00:19:37,893
Nah, winning by imitation is
still winning.

372
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:40,660
When you think about it, that's
what this girl did.

373
00:19:40,660 --> 00:19:44,693
She wasn't willing to take
risks. Instead she tried to
imitate someone who'd reached
her own dream .

374
00:19:44,726 --> 00:19:49,026
Nanako, watch! This is
how we fight for dreams.

375
00:19:49,060 --> 00:19:51,560
Copying what others do
won't get you anywhere.

376
00:19:51,626 --> 00:19:54,160
To reach your dreams,
you have to risk failure.

377
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:58,493
You gotta be yourself! Girls
have the power to make their
dreams come true.

378
00:19:58,493 --> 00:20:01,000
All we really need is
the will to try!

379
00:20:01,633 --> 00:20:08,766
Mars Flame Sniper!

380
00:20:09,733 --> 00:20:12,100
[scream]

381
00:20:12,133 --> 00:20:13,766
Now's your chance Sailor Moon!

382
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:14,733
Uhh...

383
00:20:14,766 --> 00:20:21,666
Please, Pegasus! Protect
everyone's dream!

384
00:20:21,733 --> 00:20:31,133
Twinkle Yell!

385
00:20:31,166 --> 00:20:32,666
[neigh]

386
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:53,100
Moon Gorgeous Meditation!

387
00:21:03,473 --> 00:21:08,673
Stage Out!

388
00:21:15,106 --> 00:21:16,840
This isn't over!

389
00:21:17,906 --> 00:21:19,906
Wow, Sailor Mars!
You did it!

390
00:21:26,973 --> 00:21:28,673
It's so quiet.

391
00:21:28,740 --> 00:21:30,773
Let's see... "Beauty
on the streets."

392
00:21:30,806 --> 00:21:34,073
<i>"Nanako is the hamburger</i>
<i>store's star attraction."</i>

393
00:21:34,106 --> 00:21:37,506
I'm so happy Nanako's found
her self‐confidence.

394
00:21:37,573 --> 00:21:38,773
<i>(Nanako)</i>
<i>I sure did!</i>

395
00:21:38,806 --> 00:21:41,773
<i>(Rei)</i>
<i>Nanako!</i>

396
00:21:41,806 --> 00:21:43,940
Hi, guys. I brought
you lunch.

397
00:21:43,940 --> 00:21:45,906
Looks like you're making your
own way in the world.

398
00:21:45,940 --> 00:21:50,906
Yes! Thanks to you I learned
that if I can believe in myself
I can make my own dreams come
true!

399
00:21:50,940 --> 00:21:52,906
I just have to stick with it!

400
00:21:52,940 --> 00:21:53,940
That's the spirit!

401
00:21:54,006 --> 00:21:57,340
Yeah! But I'll still need
my big sis to help me!

402
00:21:57,406 --> 00:21:58,640
Uh, wait, what?

403
00:21:58,673 --> 00:21:59,813
I'm just kidding!

404
00:21:59,846 --> 00:22:00,680
Hey!

405
00:22:00,746 --> 00:22:02,313
Looks like she fooled
you, Big Sister!

406
00:22:02,346 --> 00:22:03,646
[laughter]

407
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:05,280
C'mere, you!

408
00:22:07,080 --> 00:22:12,480
<i>(Rei)</i>
<i>Remember: Every girl has the</i>
<i>power to make her biggest dreams</i>
<i>come true.</i>

409
00:22:18,513 --> 00:22:28,480
♪

410
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:48,480
♪

411
00:22:48,480 --> 00:23:08,486
♪

412
00:23:08,486 --> 00:23:28,453
♪

